&lt;p&gt;Specialty Doctor in Anaesthesia&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from suitably qualified doctors with extensive experience in obstetric anaesthesia, the position of Specialty Doctor in Anaesthesia at ELHT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ELHT is a busy district general hospital and the department covers anaesthetic services to all major surgical specialties including general surgery, urology, orthopaedics and trauma, gynaecology, ENT and maxillofacial surgery. We are a nominated vascular centre and tertiary referral centre for HPB. There is a busy obstetric unit with around 6500 deliveries per year. There is a midwifery led unit in Blackburn (separate site) and a co-located midwifery unit and consultant led unit in Burnley. We have a 20 bedded mixed critical care unit on the Blackburn site with a 4 bedded post-operative care unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly supportive department and are firmly committed to education. We receive good feedback from trainees. We are ACSA accredited.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is the possibility for potential discussion of more than 10 PA&#39;s per week.&lt;/p&gt;
